Jeff surprises Drew with a guest appearance from his hilarious puppet, Walter.Rodney Atkins: Last we head to Nashville, Tennessee where country sensation Rodney Atkins gives us a tour of his luxury liner. Rodney also introduces us to two things he never leaves home with out. The first is his best friend, a parrot named Misty that makes some unusual noises. Then Rodney lets us check out his pride a joy, a motorcycle that he uses to drive around the cities he visits while on tour.

programme.title: Celebrity Motor Homes
programme.desc: First last we head Temecula, California, to meet up with X-Games champion and dirt bike rider, Brian Deegan. Brian gives Drew a tour of not just one, but three unique motor homes. The first is an over the top coach with a fireplace that he and his family use at the races and when on vacation. Then, Brian shows us his very first motor home that he now uses when he's riding with the guys. He's not afraid to let this RV get a little dirty. The highlight of this home away from home is a back garage where he stores and transports his mule. And last, Brian shows us the latest addition to his fleet, a hauler attached to a semi that he uses at all his races. This enormous motor home features a mechanics garage, lockers for his entire race team and an office where they can do business. The highlight of his hauler is course the garage used to store his gold medal winning dirt bikes. Drew then joins Brian for a ride on his custom-built dirt bike track right in his own backyard! Then we head to Chattanooga, Tennessee, where we catch up with one of country music's hottest young duos, Florida Georgia Line. Tyler and Brian give us a tour of their brand new 52-foot tour bus. Our first stop in this grand coach is a lounge designed to keep the party going after the show, complete with entertainment center, surround sound and automatic windows, Tyler and Brian have really decked out this space to the nines. Then the guys take us to the back of the bus where check out a their custom sleeping quarters and their favorite space on the whole bus, a back lounge which they have appropriately named "The Bat Cave." Last we arrive in Simpsonville, South Carolina, where Drew meets up with actress and country star, Jana Kramer before her show. Jana gives Drew a tour of her home on wheels that she shares with the ten guys that make up her band and crew. Jana explains to Drew that to ride on her bus, you have to be able to take a joke! That's why throughout the tour, Jana plays several practical jokes on Drew, hazing him into the club. Janna's bus features a living space that her puppy, Junior calls home, as well as a guest bathroom and bunks for all the guys.
